Responsibility

Use of SVARE in real-world systems is entirely at the user’s own responsibility.

This reference implementation provides:

• deterministic structural value resolution with reproducible value and certificate  
• value correctness from structure  
• safe handling of incomplete and conflicting structure  

It does not provide:

• computational guarantees  
• numerical stability guarantees in all environments  
• physical measurement guarantees  
• system-level execution guarantees  
• safety-critical assurances  
• regulatory or compliance guarantees  

